# Config fragment merged onto nanopi-zero2-rk3528_defconfig.
#
# Setting the boot delay to zero removes the countdown so distro-boot
# proceeds straight to extlinux.conf. Holding a key during boot still drops
# to the U-Boot prompt (abort-with-keypress), so this does not remove the
# dev escape hatch -- it just removes the wait when nobody's pressing
# anything.
#
# Do NOT add CONFIG_BOOTSTD_FULL=n or similar here: distro-boot/bootstd must
# stay enabled, since that's what finds extlinux/extlinux.conf on the first
# FAT partition of the SD card.
CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=0

# Real hardware bring-up on rock-4se (bean gosd-sz6p, 2026-07-23) found
# U-Boot scanning the global 'efi_mgr' bootmeth before extlinux on every
# boot: it probes the onboard eMMC for a Boot0000 EFI entry, fails, and
# prints ~6 lines of "Boot failed"-shaped noise before falling through to
# the extlinux bootmeth that actually works. This board hasn't had its own
# hardware bring-up yet (bean gosd-odp7), but the same Kconfig defaults
# apply: nanopi-zero2-rk3528_defconfig doesn't set this itself -- it comes
# from boot/Kconfig's `config BOOTMETH_EFI_BOOTMGR` (default y, depends on
# EFI_BOOTMGR, which defaults y for arm64) -- verified against u-boot
# v2026.07-rc5's boot/Kconfig and lib/efi_loader/Kconfig, the tag this
# board's U-Boot is pinned to (unchanged shape vs. v2026.04). Turning it off
# only drops the global efi_mgr scan; BOOTMETH_EXTLINUX (boot/Kconfig,
# `default y`, unconditional) is untouched, so extlinux discovery is
# unaffected. Unlike rock-4se, nanopi-zero2-rk3528_defconfig never sets
# CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_MMC=y, so env/Kconfig's ENV_IS_DEFAULT already resolves to
# ENV_IS_NOWHERE here by Kconfig default -- no environment-related fragment
# change needed.
# CONFIG_BOOTMETH_EFI_BOOTMGR is not set
